  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Network Engineer (AWS Focus)",
  "description": "<p>Our client is seeking an <strong>AWS Network Engineer</strong> to support and enhance their cloud and network infrastructure across hybrid environments. This role is ideal for a hands-on network professional with strong exposure to <strong>AWS networking, Palo Alto firewalls, and VPN technologies</strong>, working closely with cloud, infrastructure, and security teams.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Administer and support <strong>Palo Alto Firewalls</strong> and <strong>GlobalProtect VPN</strong></li><li>Configure and monitor <strong>AWS networking services</strong> (VPCs, Security Groups, Route Tables, NAT Gateways, Load Balancers)</li><li>Troubleshoot network incidents and service requests in line with <strong>ITIL processes</strong></li><li>Collaborate with cloud, infrastructure, and security teams to ensure secure and reliable connectivity</li><li>Maintain accurate network documentation, configurations, and change records</li><li>Communicate effectively with internal stakeholders</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Hands-on experience with the <strong>AWS cloud platform</strong></li><li>Strong knowledge of <strong>AWS networking services</strong> (VPC, NAT Gateway, Load Balancers, etc.)</li><li>Working understanding of <strong>ITIL processes</strong> (Incident, Change, Problem Management)</li><li>Strong collaboration, documentation, and communication skills</li><li><strong>Cloud and/or Network certifications</strong> (AWS, Azure, GCP, Network) are advantageous</li></ul><p><strong>To Apply</strong><br />To apply or find out more information on this role, please email us or send in your updated resume to:<br /><a href=\"#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">lynn.tay@starcareerconsulting.com</a></p><p><strong>Lynn Tay</strong> (Reg. No. R1876711)<br /><strong>STAR CAREER CONSULTING PTE LTD</strong> (EA Licence: 20C0353)</p>",
